- Oh, you're an angel.

56
00:04:17,800 --> 00:04:22,440
Boxes? - Remember, I told you a few
weeks ago, Jerry's moving to Boston.

57
00:04:22,480 --> 00:04:26,840
Oh, right! The job, the thing.
What do you do again?

58
00:04:26,920 --> 00:04:30,200
Hospital administrator.
- Right, right!

59
00:04:30,280 --> 00:04:32,120
Well, the boxes
are in my car.

60
00:04:32,200 --> 00:04:34,040
Oh, those can wait.

61
00:04:34,120 --> 00:04:36,960
I made this young man
a promise, didn't I?

62
00:04:37,000 --> 00:04:38,960
Got time to throw a few?
- Sure!

63
00:04:39,040 --> 00:04:41,440
Come on, then!

64
00:04:41,480 --> 00:04:43,840
I forgot the boyfriend was moving.
- Jerry!

65
00:04:43,880 --> 00:04:46,920
His name is Jerry!
And yes, he's moving.

66
00:04:47,000 --> 00:04:50,280
I'm sorry. I hated him less
than your other boyfriends.

67
00:04:50,360 --> 00:04:53,040
It wasn't serious, was it?
- Semiserious, yes.

68
00:04:53,120 --> 00:04:56,720
You guys aren't-
You know-

69
00:04:59,240 --> 00:05:02,000
I have been
dating him for seven months.

70
00:05:02,080 --> 00:05:04,680
What do you think?
- Really? Ooh!

71
00:05:04,720 --> 00:05:07,640
I was hoping after being married
to me you'd have no strength left.

72
00:05:07,720 --> 00:05:11,560
Remember, when we were married, I wasn't
having sex nearly as often as you were.

73
00:05:11,640 --> 00:05:15,960
Ouch! And the ref
takes a point away.

74
00:05:16,040 --> 00:05:20,200
Out!
- Max is gonna miss him.

75
00:05:20,280 --> 00:05:22,160
I'll be here.

76
00:05:22,240 --> 00:05:26,000
Ready? Yeah! Play ball.

77
00:05:26,080 --> 00:05:29,080
Max, come on. We've gotta go.

78
00:05:29,160 --> 00:05:32,960
Dad, are we really going to wrestling?
- Absolutely, Max Factor.

79
00:05:33,000 --> 00:05:35,240
We just have to stop by
the office for one minute.

80
00:05:35,280 --> 00:05:37,240
Excuse me, sir. Any spare change?

81
00:05:37,320 --> 00:05:39,240
Oh, I'm sorry. I'm all out.

82
00:05:39,280 --> 00:05:41,280
