83
00:05:41,320 --> 00:05:45,080
Fred, it's your duty to present
the strongest case possible.

84
00:05:45,160 --> 00:05:47,960
The strongest case possible
consistent with the truth.

85
00:05:48,040 --> 00:05:49,960
Will you let the judge
decide what's true?

86
00:05:50,040 --> 00:05:53,640
That's what he gets paid for.
You get paid to win.

87
00:05:53,680 --> 00:05:55,920
If you insist
that I take it to trial,

88
00:05:56,000 --> 00:05:59,560
I will represent Mrs. Cole
aggressively and ethically.

89
00:05:59,640 --> 00:06:01,720
But Miranda, I won't lie.

90
00:06:03,680 --> 00:06:06,640
Then we'll just have
to find someone who will.

91
00:06:08,640 --> 00:06:10,920
Twenty-first floor.
Men's wear.

92
00:06:15,160 --> 00:06:17,320
Hi, Mr. Reede!
- Whoa!

93
00:06:17,360 --> 00:06:21,320
Hey. Did you do something
to your hair?

94
00:06:21,360 --> 00:06:23,120
It's a bit extreme,
isn't it?

95
00:06:23,200 --> 00:06:26,760
No! That's the thing nowadays, right?

96
00:06:26,800 --> 00:06:30,120
He said it would accent my facial
features. - That's what it does!

97
00:06:30,160 --> 00:06:32,840
It completely accents
your facial features.

98
00:06:32,880 --> 00:06:37,120
We're just gonna go
to my office-

99
00:06:38,920 --> 00:06:41,400
Hey, Fletcher.
- Hey, Pete.

100
00:06:41,480 --> 00:06:43,800
You losin' a little weight?
- I don't know. Maybe.

101
00:06:43,880 --> 00:06:46,280
Looks and personality.
A double-threat guy.

102
00:06:46,360 --> 00:06:48,680
Hey, Mr. Reede.
- Hey... man.

103
00:06:48,720 --> 00:06:50,720
It's, uh, Randy.
- Yeah, I know.

104
00:06:50,760 --> 00:06:53,720
Takin' lunch orders.
Anything?

105
00:06:53,800 --> 00:06:55,760
No, thanks.

106
00:06:55,840 --> 00:06:59,120
I had so much for breakfast,
I'm ready to pop.

107
00:06:59,200 --> 00:07:03,280
I mean, I'm full.
- Okay. Great.

108
00:07:07,200 --> 00:07:09,920
Max!
- Hi, Greta.

109
00:07:09,960 --> 00:07:14,520
Hey, what's new? - It's my birthday
tomorrow, and we're having a party.

110
00:07:14,600 --> 00:07:17,800
Wow! I am sure your daddy
has got you something wonderful.

111
00:07:17,880 --> 00:07:23,240
Yeah?
- Yeah, you bet! Listen, kiddo.

112
00:07:23,320 --> 00:07:27,480
Why don't you play in my office
for a minute. Sue somebody for
everything they've got.

113
00:07:27,560 --> 00:07:31,640
Maybe you can send a fax
to one of your girlfriends. Hey, sorry.

114
00:07:31,720 --> 00:07:35,440
Damn it!
I completely forgot.

115
00:07:35,520 --> 00:07:37,400
Oh, what a surprise.

116
00:07:37,480 --> 00:07:40,040
You are a saint.
I should buy you a gift.

117
00:07:40,080 --> 00:07:43,960
You did. - I always do
the classy thing. Any calls?

118
00:07:44,040 --> 00:07:46,920
The Drawlings' clerk needs your filing.
- Tell him it's in the mail.

119
00:07:46,960 --> 00:07:51,720
Right. You'll do it next week. Mr. McKinley
phoned to confirm your meeting tomorrow.

120
00:07:51,800 --> 00:07:54,720
Strep throat. Some kind of virus.
What's goin' around?

121
00:07:54,760 --> 00:07:56,800
Asian flu?
- Good one.

122
00:07:56,840 --> 00:07:59,400
And your mother called.
- I'm on vacation.

123
00:07:59,440 --> 00:08:01,800
It's your fifth week.
- Snowed in. Phones are down.

124
00:08:01,840 --> 00:08:04,200
Break mother's heart.
Done. That's it.

125
00:08:04,280 --> 00:08:07,120
Except Miranda's looking for you.

126
00:08:07,200 --> 00:08:11,560
How much ass do I have to kiss
to make partner?

127
00:08:11,600 --> 00:08:16,040
Tell her I broke my leg and I had to be
shot. - Tell her yourself.

128
00:08:16,080 --> 00:08:20,040
And then send out a notice
of judgement on my win today!

129
00:08:20,080 --> 00:08:25,160
I'll get right on it.
- Miranda! Hey, I didn't see you.

130
00:08:25,200 --> 00:08:27,560
You look beautiful today.

131
00:08:27,640 --> 00:08:30,080
Here! I bought you a gift.

132
00:08:30,120 --> 00:08:33,840
Oh, thanks. I heard about
your victory. Congratulations.

133
00:08:33,920 --> 00:08:37,320
You're making quite an impression
on the partnership committee.

134
00:08:38,480 --> 00:08:41,760
That's right!
You folks are meetin' soon.

135
00:08:41,800 --> 00:08:44,040
I've been so busy,
I haven't even thought about it.

136
00:08:47,360 --> 00:08:49,880
Anyway. I have a client
in my office.

137
00:08:49,960 --> 00:08:54,760
Better not keep him waiting.
- Actually, something rather
important's just come up.

138
00:08:54,800 --> 00:08:57,880
Um, you're not busy tonight, are you?

139
00:09:04,720 --> 00:09:06,800
We're not going, are we?

140
00:09:20,160 --> 00:09:23,920
Audrey. You know how there are
moments you know are critical?

141
00:09:24,000 --> 00:09:26,920
Mm-hmm.
- And choices that have to be made...

142
00:09:27,000 --> 00:09:30,280
upon which all one's
future happiness will depend?

143
00:09:30,320 --> 00:09:32,240
This is one of those moments.

144
00:09:34,000 --> 00:09:37,440
What are you
trying to say?

145
00:09:37,480 --> 00:09:39,840
Will you marry me?

146
00:09:43,240 --> 00:09:47,200
You're moving. - I know, but
l want you and Max to come with me.

147
00:09:47,240 --> 00:09:49,320
Audrey, I've been giving this
a lot of thought.

148
00:09:49,360 --> 00:09:52,200
You know I'm not prone to wild
flights of romantic fancy.

149
00:09:52,280 --> 00:09:56,480
But the thought of you and I
together just makes sense.

150
00:09:56,520 --> 00:09:59,280
Now I'm ready. I think
you're ready. I love Max.

151
00:09:59,360 --> 00:10:01,560
You love Max.
It's right. It fits.

152
00:10:02,720 --> 00:10:05,080
So what do you say?

153
00:10:21,640 --> 00:10:25,000
Hey, creepy.
Happy birthday.

154
00:10:25,080 --> 00:10:26,920
How old are you now,
22 or 23?

155
00:10:27,000 --> 00:10:30,320
I'm five, Dad.
- Okay.

156
00:10:30,400 --> 00:10:32,880
Return the beer keg.

157
00:10:32,960 --> 00:10:35,960
Cancel the dancing girls.

158
00:10:36,040 --> 00:10:38,880
I don't know what I'm gonna do.

159
00:10:38,920 --> 00:10:41,400
I feel completely unprepared
for this.

160
00:10:41,480 --> 00:10:44,200
You see, I bought you a present,
but last night...

161
00:10:44,240 --> 00:10:47,400
I accidentally swallowed it.

162
00:10:47,480 --> 00:10:50,080
Dad, it's in your belly!
- Scalpel.

163
00:10:51,120 --> 00:10:53,000
I hope it's not
partially digested!

164
00:10:53,040 --> 00:10:55,440
Ooh! Look out!

165
00:10:55,520 --> 00:10:58,080
Cool! What is it?
- Cool!

166
00:10:58,120 --> 00:11:01,680
It's- lt's a surprise.

167
00:11:01,760 --> 00:11:03,600
All right, it's a pony.
Just open it!

168
00:11:05,000 --> 00:11:08,200
I'm gonna help,
'cause I can't stand it!

169
00:11:09,680 --> 00:11:12,880
Baseball stuff!
- Baseball stuff!

170
00:11:12,960 --> 00:11:15,560
Cool! Can we play?

171
00:11:15,640 --> 00:11:19,200
I'll be Nomo. You can be
Jose Canseco. Can we play?

172
00:11:19,240 --> 00:11:21,640
Absolutely.
- Yeah!

173
00:11:21,680 --> 00:11:25,440
Right after your party
tonight, we'll do it.

174
00:11:25,480 --> 00:11:28,040
You and me.

175
00:11:28,120 --> 00:11:31,280
I just have to really
concentrate on this right now.

176
00:11:53,320 --> 00:11:55,720
Hi!

177
00:11:55,800 --> 00:11:58,800
Hey! Happy birthday.

178
00:11:58,920 --> 00:12:02,440
Thanks, Mom.
- Happy birthday, Max!

179
00:12:02,440 --> 00:12:07,000
One, two, three, four, five.
And one for good luck!

180
00:12:07,040 --> 00:12:09,000
He struck the child.
Did you see that?

181
00:12:09,080 --> 00:12:12,480
Look at what Dad got me!
- Whoa! Great!

182
00:12:12,520 --> 00:12:15,400
Hey, I have my glove
in the car.

183
00:12:15,480 --> 00:12:18,720
Maybe we can stop at the park
on the way home and play catch.

184
00:12:18,760 --> 00:12:22,160
Then tonight we can rub oil in it
and wrap a big rubber band around it.

185
00:12:22,240 --> 00:12:24,880
It'll be great.
Hey, great gift, Dad!

186
00:12:24,960 --> 00:12:29,040
Thanks, son. I'm so glad my gift
could bring those two together.

187
00:12:29,120 --> 00:12:32,000
My plan to phase myself out
is almost complete.

188
00:12:33,280 --> 00:12:35,360
Something's come up,
and we need to talk.

189
00:12:35,400 --> 00:12:37,600
Come on, Mom.
I want to go play!

190
00:12:37,680 --> 00:12:40,680
And actually it's kind of important,
so maybe we could talk tonight?

191
00:12:40,760 --> 00:12:42,760
Tonight?
- Yes.

192
00:12:42,840 --> 00:12:45,760
Max's birthday party.
- Oh! Yeah.

193
00:12:45,800 --> 00:12:48,200
Sure. Of course.
We'll talk then. Great!

194
00:12:50,800 --> 00:12:53,400
Maximus! I'm outta here.
- Bye, Dad.

195
00:12:53,440 --> 00:12:55,760
Jerry, enjoy my wife.

196
00:13:11,040 --> 00:13:13,480
Well, this is good.

197
00:13:13,560 --> 00:13:15,840
This is really smart.

198
00:13:15,880 --> 00:13:17,760
Thank you.
- Only-

199
00:13:17,800 --> 00:13:22,160
Well, it's not true.
Does that present a problem?

200
00:13:23,760 --> 00:13:25,600
Mrs. Cole,
the only problem here...

201
00:13:25,680 --> 00:13:29,280
is that after you've provided years
of faithful service and loving support,

202
00:13:29,320 --> 00:13:31,440
of raising his children-
they are his?

203
00:13:31,520 --> 00:13:35,560
Huh? Oh. Yeah, yeah.
One for sure.

204
00:13:37,040 --> 00:13:39,360
After all that, your husband
wants to deny you...

205
00:13:39,400 --> 00:13:43,600
a fair share of the assets based
on one act of indiscretion. - Seven.

206
00:13:43,680 --> 00:13:47,640
Pardon me?
- Seven single acts of indiscretion.

207
00:13:48,800 --> 00:13:50,640
Seven acts of indiscretion,

208
00:13:50,720 --> 00:13:52,920
only one of which he has
any evidence of...

209
00:13:52,960 --> 00:13:56,400
and all of which he himself
is responsible for.

210
00:13:56,480 --> 00:13:59,600
He is?
- Mrs. Cole.

211
00:13:59,680 --> 00:14:03,360
You're the victim here.
The wife of a cold, distant workaholic.

212
00:14:03,400 --> 00:14:05,960
Starved for affection, driven
into the arms of another man!

213
00:14:06,040 --> 00:14:07,920
Seven.
- Yeah, whatever!

214
00:14:08,000 --> 00:14:10,080
You're not trying to deny him
what is rightfully his.

215
00:14:10,160 --> 00:14:13,480
All you're insisting on is what
is rightfully yours. - Yeah.

216
00:14:13,560 --> 00:14:16,440
And maybe a...
fraction more.

217
00:14:16,480 --> 00:14:18,880
I think you're
bending over backwards.

218
00:14:18,960 --> 00:14:23,640
Yeah. I did offer to
give him joint custody of the kids.

219
00:14:23,680 --> 00:14:26,720
He is, after all,
a wonderful father.

220
00:14:26,760 --> 00:14:29,840
And how does he repay you?

221
00:14:29,920 --> 00:14:32,160
By dragging you through
a painful litigation process!

222
00:14:32,200 --> 00:14:35,680
No, no, no, no!
This can't happen!

223
00:14:35,760 --> 00:14:39,320
With all due respect, this isn't
about you and Mr. Cole anymore.

224
00:14:39,360 --> 00:14:41,280
This is about all women.

225
00:14:41,320 --> 00:14:44,640
Where would Tina Turner be right
now if she'd rolled over and said,

226
00:14:44,680 --> 00:14:47,840
<i><b>Hit me again, lke,
and put some stank on it?</b></i>

227
00:14:47,880 --> 00:14:49,960
Rollin' on the river,
that's where she'd be.

228
00:14:50,040 --> 00:14:53,920
But she's beyond Thunderdome,
because she decided to send a message.

229
00:14:53,960 --> 00:14:58,680
Wake up, sisters!
There's no-o-o-o-o-o...

230
00:14:58,720 --> 00:15:02,240
such thing as a weaker sex!

231
00:15:02,280 --> 00:15:05,680
You know what?

232
00:15:05,760 --> 00:15:10,240
You're right, Mr. Reede. I am
tired of getting kicked around!

233
00:15:10,280 --> 00:15:12,800
Good for you!

234
00:15:12,880 --> 00:15:16,840
Thank you.
I am so grateful...

235
00:15:16,920 --> 00:15:19,720
to have an attorney
I can trust.

236
00:15:26,200 --> 00:15:28,040
Oh, you are good.

237
00:15:28,120 --> 00:15:32,680
You are very, very good.

238
00:15:32,760 --> 00:15:36,560
